We could write a collective poem, expressing our gratitude and hopes. What do you think?"\nExample 1: "Gregg, I\'m so sorry, but my fiancée and I have decided to elope. We want an intimate, spontaneous ceremony, just the two of us. I know it\'s last minute, but we\'re following our hearts. I promise to make it up to you, maybe a post-wedding celebration?"\nExample 2: "Ah, come on, Kenton! Let\'s catch up soon, but not about the past, okay?"\nExample 4: "Aww, no worries, Endia! I\'ve been amazing, just got back from a beach trip and it was incredible! How about you, what\'s new in your world?"\nExample 5: "Oh, Jaida, I\'m thrilled you feel the same way! I\'ve been dying to explore the possibilities of us too. Don\'t be such a buzzkill!"\nExample 7: "Ah, it was like being in a nightmare, but one that felt so real. I was trapped, and the flames were closing in.
